snippet: Prime Minister Wen Jiabao delivered a sometimes gloomy assessment of the state of Chinese society in his final annual work report to the national legislature.

byline.original: By ANDREW JACOBS and CHRIS BUCKLEY

lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Wen Jiabao delivered a sometimes gloomy assessment of the state of Chinese society in his final annual work report to the national legislature.

headline.seo: On Eve of People’s Congress in China, Vows of Change and Raised Hopes
headline.main: China’s Wen Warns of Inequality and Vows to Continue Military Buildup
